blocks.name: ordiso
blocks.content: Order-isomorphic ordinal numbers are equal. (Contributed by Jeff Hankins, 16-Oct-2009.) (Proof shortened by Mario Carneiro, 24-Jun-2015.)
blocks.origin:
thm ordiso(setvar s0, class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wa(wcel(c0, con0), wcel(c1, con0)), wb(wceq(c0, c1), wex(s0, wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c1))))
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
} = {
  impbid(wa(wcel(c0, con0), wcel(c1, con0)), wceq(c0, c1), wex(s0, wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c1)))
  syl5ibcom(wa(wcel(c0, con0), wcel(c1, con0)), wceq(c0, c1), wex(s0, wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c1)), wex(s0, wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c0)))
  adantr(wcel(c0, con0), wcel(c1, con0), wex(s0, wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c0)))
  mpisyl(wcel(c0, con0), wex(s0, wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c0)), wcel(cres(cid, c0), universe), wiso(cres(cid, c0), cep, cep, c0, c0))
  resiexg(c0, con0)
  isoid(c0, cep)
  spcegv(s0, cres(cid, c0), universe, wiso(cres(cid, c0), cep, cep, c0, c0), wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c0))
  isoeq1(cv(s0), cres(cid, c0), cep, cep, c0, c0)
  exbidv(s0, wceq(c0, c1), wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c0), wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c1))
  isoeq5(c0, c1, cv(s0), cep, cep, c0)
  exlimdv(s0, wa(wcel(c0, con0), wcel(c1, con0)), wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c1), wceq(c0, c1))
  syl2an(wcel(c0, con0), wcel(c1, con0), wi(wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c1), wceq(c0, c1)), word(c0), word(c1))
  eloni(c0)
  eloni(c1)
  3expia(word(c0), word(c1), wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c1), wceq(c0, c1))
  3coml(word(c0), word(c1), wiso(cv(s0), cep, cep, c0, c1), wceq(c0, c1))
  ordiso2(cv(s0), c0, c1)
  diff.wiso.s(s0, cres(cid, c0), cep, cep, c0, c0)
  diff.cres.s(s0, cid, c0)
  diff.cid.s(s0)
  diff.cep.s(s0)
  diff.wceq.s(s0, c0, c1)
  diff.wa.s(s0, wcel(c0, con0), wcel(c1, con0))
  diff.wcel.s(s0, c0, con0)
  diff.wcel.s(s0, c1, con0)
  diff.con0.s(s0)
}

blocks.name: ordtypelem9
blocks.content: Lemma for ~ ordtype . Either the function ` OrdIso ` is an isomorphism onto all of ` A ` , or ` OrdIso ` is not a set, which by ~ oif implies that either ` ran O C_ A ` is a proper class or ` dom O = On ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 25-Jun-2015.)

blocks.name: ordtype2
blocks.content: For any set-like well-ordered class, if the order isomorphism exists (is a set), then it maps some ordinal onto ` A ` isomorphically. Otherwise, ` F ` is a proper class, which implies that either ` ran F C_ A ` is a proper class or ` dom F = On ` . This weak version of ~ ordtype does not require the Axiom of Replacement. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 25-Jun-2015.)

blocks.content: When ` A ` is a subclass of ` On ` , ` F ` is a strictly monotone ordinal functions, and it is also complete (it is an isomorphism onto all of ` A ` ). The proof avoids ~ ax-rep (the second statement is trivial under ~ ax-rep ). (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 26-Jun-2015.)

blocks.name: oiid

blocks.name: hartogs
blocks.content: Given any set, the Hartogs number of the set is the least ordinal not dominated by that set. This theorem proves that there is always an ordinal which satisfies this. (This theorem can be proven trivially using the AC - see theorem ~ ondomon - but this proof works in ZF.) (Contributed by Jeff Hankins, 22-Oct-2009.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 15-May-2015.)

blocks.name: wemappo
blocks.content: Construct lexicographic order on a function space based on a well-ordering of the indices and a total ordering of the values. Without totality on the values or least differing indices, the best we can prove here is a partial order. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 18-Jan-2015.)

blocks.name: wemapso2
blocks.content: An alternative to having a well-order on ` R ` in ~ wemapso is to restrict the function set to finitely-supported functions. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 8-Feb-2015.) (Revised by AV, 1-Jul-2019.)
blocks.origin:
thm wemapso2(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, setvar s3, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, class c6, class c7) {
  |- wi(w3a(wcel(c0, c1), wor(c2, c0), wor(c3, c4)), wor(c5, c6))
  -| wceq(c5, copab(s0, s1, wrex(s2, c0, wa(wbr(cfv(cv(s0), cv(s2)), c3, cfv(cv(s1), cv(s2))), wral(s3, c0, wi(wbr(cv(s3), c2, cv(s2)), wceq(cfv(cv(s0), cv(s3)), cfv(cv(s1), cv(s3)))))))))
  -| wceq(c6, crab(s0, co(c4, cmap, c0), wbr(cv(s0), cfsupp, c7)))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffss(s0, s3)
  -| diffss(s1, s2)
  -| diffss(s1, s3)
  -| diffss(s2, s3)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c2)
  -| diffsc(s0, c3)
  -| diffsc(s0, c4)
  -| diffsc(s0, c7)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c2)
  -| diffsc(s1, c3)
  -| diffsc(s2, c0)
  -| diffsc(s2, c2)
  -| diffsc(s2, c3)
  -| diffsc(s3, c0)
  -| diffsc(s3, c2)
  -| diffsc(s3, c3)
} = {
  pm2.61i(wi(w3a(wcel(c0, c1), wor(c2, c0), wor(c3, c4)), wor(c5, c6)), wcel(c7, universe))
  expcom(wcel(c7, universe), w3a(wcel(c0, c1), wor(c2, c0), wor(c3, c4)), wor(c5, c6))
  wemapso2lem(s0, s1, s2, s3, c0, c1, c2, c3, c4, c7, universe, c5, c6)
  a1d(wn(wcel(c7, universe)), w3a(wcel(c0, c1), wor(c2, c0), wor(c3, c4)), wor(c5, c6))
  mpbiri(wn(wcel(c7, universe)), wor(c5, c6), wor(c5, emptycls))
  so0(c5)
  syl(wn(wcel(c7, universe)), wb(wor(c5, c6), wor(c5, emptycls)), wceq(c6, emptycls))
  syl5eq(c6, emptycls, crab(s0, co(c4, cmap, c0), wbr(cv(s0), cfsupp, c7)), wn(wcel(c7, universe)))
  sylibr(wn(wcel(c7, universe)), wceq(crab(s0, co(c4, cmap, c0), wbr(cv(s0), cfsupp, c7)), emptycls), wral(s0, co(c4, cmap, c0), wn(wbr(cv(s0), cfsupp, c7))))
  ralrimivw(s0, co(c4, cmap, c0), wn(wcel(c7, universe)), wn(wbr(cv(s0), cfsupp, c7)))
  con3i(wcel(c7, universe), wbr(cv(s0), cfsupp, c7))
  brrelex2i(cv(s0), cfsupp, c7)
  relfsupp()
  rabeq0(s0, co(c4, cmap, c0), wbr(cv(s0), cfsupp, c7))
  soeq2(c6, emptycls, c5)
  diff.wn.s(s0, wcel(c7, universe))
  diff.wcel.s(s0, c7, universe)
  diff.universe.s(s0)
}
